edu.caltech.sbw
Class Service

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--edu.caltech.sbw.Service
public class Service
extends java.lang.Object

The Service class represents a service, an interface to resources inside a module. Obtaining an instance of a Service object implies that a module implementing the service has been launched by the SBW Broker.

Version:
$Revision: 1.7 $
Author:
Michael Hucka, $Author: mhucka $

Method Detail

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object other)
Indicates whether some other object is "equal to" this one. This method implements equality for Service objects, overriding the method of the same name on the basic Java Object class. If the given object is a Service object, and both its module instance identifier is equal to this service's module and its service identifier is equal to this service, then this method returns true, else it returns false. This equivalence means that the two module proxy objects refer to the same running instance of a module.

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object
Parameters:
other - the object with which to compare this one.
Returns:
true if the argument is a Service object that refers to the same service as this object, false otherwise.
See Also:
Object.equals(java.lang.Object)

Returns:
a service descriptor object describing this service
Throws:

SBWModuleNotFoundException - if the SBW Broker cannot find the module that is supposed to implement this service
SBWServiceNotFoundException - if the service corresponding to this service descriptor cannot be found on the corresponding module
SBWException - if another problem arises during the execution of this method

getMethod

public ServiceMethod getMethod(java.lang.String nameAndArgs)
                        throws SBWCommunicationException,
                               SBWMethodAmbiguousException,
                               SBWSignatureSyntaxException
Returns a ServiceMethod object corresponding to the single method described by the partial signature nameAndArgs. The parameter may consist of only a method name, or a name and arguments or a complete signature. Formally nameAndArgs has the syntax: 
SName
or the syntax: 
   [ReturnType Space] SName Space? '(' VarArgList ')'
where the arguments list is used to locate specific methods with the same name. The optional return type is ignored when matching signatures. If the syntax is incorrect, this method will throw SBWSignatureSyntaxException.

The given name (and optional arguments) is compared to the parsed signatures of the methods on the service. If more than one method on the service matches the given argument, this method throws SBWMethodAmbiguousException.

Since obtaining the method list requires contacting the module instance and the SBW Broker, this method may throw an SBWCommunicationException if something goes wrong during communications.

Parameters:
nameAndArgs - a string giving the name and optionally the arguments of the method being sought
Throws:
SBWCommunicationException - if a communications problem occurs in contacting the SBW Broker or the module
SBWMethodAmbiguousException - if the given partial signature is not enough to disambiguate between multiple candidate methods provided by the service
SBWSignatureSyntaxException - if the syntax of parameter nameAndArgs is incorrect

getModule

public Module getModule()
Returns a Module class object corresponding to the module that implements this service. Since the module instance must already be running, this action does not result in a new instance being launched; however, it does create a new object of class Module referring to the same instance.

Returns:
the Module object representing the module that implements this service

getServiceObject

public java.lang.Object getServiceObject(java.lang.Class interfaceClass)
                                  throws SBWCommunicationException,
                                         SBWServiceNotFoundException,
                                         SBWMethodNotFoundException,
                                         SBWUnsupportedObjectTypeException
Returns a proxy object for this service. The proxy object will have the interface specified by argument interfaceClass. The methods of this object will be the methods specified by the interface.

Parameters:
interfaceClass - the definition of the interface to be used for constructing the proxy

getServiceObject

public java.lang.Object getServiceObject(java.lang.Class[] interfaceClasses)
                                  throws SBWCommunicationException,
                                         SBWServiceNotFoundException,
                                         SBWMethodAmbiguousException,
                                         SBWMethodNotFoundException,
                                         SBWUnsupportedObjectTypeException
Returns a proxy object for this service. The proxy object will have the interface specified by the union of the arguments interfaceClasses. The methods of this object will be the methods specified by the set of interfaces.

Implementation note: this uses the handy Proxy class to implement an object that acts as a proxy for the remote service.

Parameters:
interfaceClasses - array of interface classes, to be used in defining the interface of the proxy object returned.
Throws:
SBWCommunicationException - if a communications problem occurs in contacting the SBW Broker or the module
SBWServiceNotFoundException - if the service corresponding to this service descriptor cannot be found on the corresponding module
SBWMethodAmbiguousException - if the same method appears in more than one of the interfaces in argument interfaceClasses
SBWMethodNotFoundException - if one or more of the methods in the set of interfaces in interfaceClasses has no equivalent in this service
SBWUnsupportedObjectTypeException - if there is an unsupported data type in a method declaration in the set of interfaces in interfaceClasses
